text: Porozal is a district of the Cañas canton, in the Guanacaste province of Costa Rica. == History == Porozal was created on 30 November 1995 by Decreto Ejecutivo 24809-G. Segregated from Cañas. == Geography == Porozal has an area of km² and an elevation of metres. ==Villages== Administrative center of the district is the village of Porozal. Other villages in the district Brisas, Eskameca, Guapinol, Pozas, Puerto Alegre, Quesera, Santa Lucía, Taboga (partly) and Tiquirusas. == Demographics == For the 2011 census, Porozal had a population of inhabitants. == Transportation == === Road transportation === The district is covered by the following road routes: *25px National Route 18 == References == Category:Districts of Guanacaste Province Category:Populated places in Guanacaste Province
